														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1092887">
									

<blockquote>
<p>as it's a blatant attempt to inflate the importance of your SCP</p>
</blockquote>
<p>No, it's not.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Do you really need that much technobabble to explain how it infiltrates a house and electrocutes individuals?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>What can I cut while still giving the reader a clear indication of how dangerous the entity is at a given time?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Does it really need to "hunt" certain individuals, making them paranoid in the process?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>With the motive I've got in mind for it, yes, it would hunt specific individuals. However, there's no way for the Foundation to know this motive, so I don't specify it.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>(Besides, that just borders on "things what make people go crazy".)</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This does not drive ordinary people crazy "because lol." If you knew or suspected you were being followed at all times, and furthermore believed you saw things which showed up in no photograph, you might be a tad bit unsettled.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>It's not a comprehensive explanation of how something is contained, it's a quick and dirty briefing in case something goes horribly wrong and we need to know RIGHT NOW how to make sure something is safely contained.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>If it gets out of the capacitor bank, you're in for some fun any way you cut it. That's why the containment procedures are so thorough - to ensure this doesn't happen. There's no "quick and dirty" containment stratagem for 500MJ of electrical energy.</p>

							</div>

								
					
