			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1093751">
									

<p>Focus on the point you are trying to make or the reaction you want to get from the reader, and cut out or move anything that does not promote that reaction even if it is perfectly logical. You're more than good enough at writing out the kind of documentation a top secret science conspiracy would write, you need to switch gears to story-telling disguised as documentation.</p>
<p>Make your containment procedures much simpler but keep in the part about the presence of blood being perfectly normal — that is fantastic first step in setting the mood — then tell us what the thing is in as concise a description as possible. It's a hostile energy being that is incredibly hard to contain due to its nature. its motives are inscrutable and it is capable of doing a lot more damage than it is currently doing. Ditch anything in the description that doesn't convey that point directly. Then hit the reader with the final twist, where this thing creatively murdered its protected target by staging a false emergency call prior to triggering an actual heart attack.</p>

