<p>Did the math. You need to know the voltage your capacitor supports to be able to convert farads to joules.<br />
Your entity's energy is 513 megajoules.<br />
An industrial capacitor (I chose EPCOS B4345, because it was frequently mentioned) can store around 1200 joules. Ergo, 427&#160;500 capacitors, around 2&#160;kg each. That's a train load of'em.<br />
Russian К75-100 can offer the 19kJ you mention, but they're 33kg each. Also a train load.</p>

