				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="1472934"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1368086927 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">09 May 2013 08:08</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1770050">
									

<p>I don't get this. <em>Why</em> does it ooze blood? That detail is mentioned in the containment procedures, then never comes up again, and seems to have nothing to do with anything. Also, how is it &quot;predatory&quot;? I get that it likes to electrocute people, but <em>why</em>? If I had to guess, I'd say because it feeds on neural impulses somehow, but that's only vaguely implied. Also, what was with those two known cases of people who could be resuscitated - if it <em>does</em> feed on neural impulses, why didn't it feed on the neural energy of those two? Furthermore, technobabble sails right over my head, so I have no sense of how powerful this thing is supposed to be; I mean, it can silently follow people, but it's also somehow powerful or something…? I also don't get how many there are - is there just one, or is this a widespread species of some sort that the Foundation has yet to contain all of?</p>
<p>I <em>did</em> pick up on SCP-938 making that emergency call to try to save its target's life; but, again, <em>why</em> would it do that? What does it want from its &quot;targets&quot;? Does it just enjoy making people paranoid? Is the paranoia a <em>direct</em> result of being followed by SCP-938, or does being followed by SCP-938 leave little hints that unsettle the targets?</p>
<p>Leaving out just enough information to make the reader's imagination do all the work is a fine art, and if you leave out too much, you don't leave them with anything to work with, you just leave them with a general feeling of &quot;WTF?&quot;. Downvoted for being the kind of thing that incites a &quot;WTF?&quot; response.</p>

							</div>

								
					
